#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

cat <<'HELP'
Tmux UX Cheatsheet
==================

Main/watcher pattern:
  1) Put your primary CLI work in pane 0 (main)
  2) Keep pane 1 as watcher/reader
  3) From watcher pane, read/copy main pane quickly:
     tmux-pane-read --main --stdout
     tmux-pane-read --main --copy

Other capture commands:
  tmux-pane-read --last --copy
  tmux-pane-read --active --lines 3000 --stdout
  tmux-pane-read --target %3 --lines 3000 --copy

Layout commands:
  tmux-layout-apply main-watch
  tmux-layout-apply pair
  tmux-layout-apply dev-triple
  tmux-layout-apply tiled

Inside tmux keybindings:
  Prefix + ?    Open this help
  Prefix + y    Copy last pane (@pane_read_lines, default 3000)
  Prefix + Y    Preview last pane capture
  Prefix + 1    Apply main-watch layout
  Prefix + 2    Apply pair layout
  Prefix + 3    Apply tiled layout
  Prefix + r    Reload tmux config

Notes:
  - Captured text is always stored in tmux buffer.
  - 'main' target means pane 0 of the current window.
  - Line count precedence: --lines > TMUX_PANE_READ_LINES > tmux @pane_read_lines > 3000.
HELP
